  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Mountain of the House of the LORD"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the last days the mountain of the house of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be established as the chief of the mountains;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "it will be raised above the hills,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the peoples will stream to it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And many nations will come and say:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Come, let us go up to the mountain of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to the house of the God of Jacob.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will teach us His ways,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we may walk in His paths.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "For the law will go forth from Zion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the word of the LORD from Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then He will judge between many peoples",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and arbitrate for strong nations far and wide.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then they will beat their swords into plowshares",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their spears into pruning hooks.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Nation will no longer take up the sword against nation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will they train anymore for war.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And each man will sit under his own vine",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and under his own fig tree,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with no one to frighten him.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "For the mouth of the LORD of Hosts has spoken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though each of the peoples",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may walk in the name of his god,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "yet we will walk in the name of the LORD our God",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "forever and ever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Restoration of Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“On that day,” declares the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“I will gather the lame;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will assemble the outcast,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even those whom I have afflicted.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And I will make the lame into a remnant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the outcast into a strong nation.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then the LORD will rule over them in Mount Zion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from that day and forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And you, O watchtower of the flock,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O stronghold",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3819
          },
          {
            "text": "of the Daughter of Zion—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the former dominion will be restored to you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "sovereignty will come to the Daughter of Jerusalem.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do you now cry aloud?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Is there no king among you?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Has your counselor perished",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that anguish grips you like a woman in labor?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Writhe in agony, O Daughter of Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a woman in labor.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For now you will leave the city",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and camp in the open fields.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You will go to Babylon;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there you will be rescued;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "there the LORD will redeem you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the hand of your enemies!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But now many nations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "have assembled against you,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "saying, “Let her be defiled,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and let us feast our eyes on Zion.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But they do not know the thoughts of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or understand His plan,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for He has gathered them",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like sheaves to the threshing floor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rise and thresh, O Daughter of Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for I will give you horns of iron",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and hooves of bronze",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to break to pieces many peoples.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Then you will devote",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3820
          },
          {
            "text": "their gain to the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their wealth to the Lord of all the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
